Reasoning: The paper deals with graph searching games, which are closely related to graph decompositions and associated width measures. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on digraphs and directed tree-width suggests that cs.DM and cs.DS are the most likely categories, followed by cs.CG and cs.GT. The algorithmic applicability of digraph decompositions also suggests cs.AI as a possible category.
